description:
Paul didn’t choose easy places to minister and he made his way to Athens, a centre of commerce and philosophy. Here Paul met with the locals and on Mars Hill, just across from the Acropolis he would have spoken to some of the brightest minds in his day. It wasn’t easy but Paul use of tact, skill and patience gives us an example to use today in our witness and ministry.
